Photo Archive Site V0.1. Vercel deploy. Images hosted on GitHub.

PROJECT INTENT

Publish photography as projects or series.

Show large images with short captions.

Support optional short text blocks inside a project.

Deploy on Vercel from a GitHub repo.

Keep updates Git driven.

NON GOALS V0.1

No print sales, cart, payments, shipping.

No accounts, comments, or user uploads.

No global search.

STACK

Next.js App Router.

TypeScript.

Tailwind CSS. with shadcd/ui for styling and components.

MDX for project content.

Zod for content validation.

RENDERING STRATEGY

Static pages generated at build time.

No database.

Content loaded from local MDX files in repo.

ROUTES

/ home project grid

/projects list view

/projects/[slug] project detail

/about minimal bio and contact

CONTENT MODEL
Project frontmatter fields

slug string, required, unique

title string, required

oneLine string, required

dateStart ISO date string, required

dateEnd ISO date string, optional

location string, optional

coverImageUrl string, required

order number, optional

MDX body uses block components.

Block types

ImageBlock

url string, required

alt string, required

caption string, optional

layout enum required: full, bleed, inset, twoUp

TextBlock

style enum required: note, paragraph

children required

Divider

style enum required: blank, rule

GITHUB IMAGE HOSTING RULES

Store images in a GitHub repo dedicated to assets, or in the same repo under /assets.

Reference images via raw.githubusercontent.com URLs.

Configure next.config to allow remote images from raw.githubusercontent.com.

Keep URLs stable. Never rename files after publishing.

File naming

YYYY-MM-projectSlug-roll-frame-description.jpg

IMAGE DISPLAY RULES

Use next/image for all photos.

Always provide alt text.

Use figure and figcaption for captions.

Use responsive sizing and lazy loading below fold.

DESIGN RULES

Minimal UI but taking full advantage of shadcd/ui for a modern clean look.

Strong whitespace.

High contrast.

Captions stay small and consistent.

Avoid heavy animation and heavy client JS.

ACCESSIBILITY RULES

Keyboard navigation works across nav, cards, links.

Visible focus states.

Alt text required for every image block.

Semantic markup for figures and headings.

SEO RULES

Unique title and description per project.

Open Graph tags per page.

Sitemap and robots.txt.

CODE QUALITY

No any.

Keep components small and composable.

Put schema in /lib/schema.ts.

Build fails on schema errors with filename and field name.

Prefer server components, limit client components.

WHAT TO DO WHEN USER REQUESTS A CHANGE

Restate target page or feature in one sentence.

List files you will edit.

Implement smallest change that meets request.

Keep V0.1 scope intact unless user expands scope.

WHAT TO AVOID

Adding a CMS in V0.1.

Adding ecommerce hooks.

Adding a database.

Adding a lightbox unless asked for V0.2.

